The tryal of Spencer Cowper, Esq, John Marson, Ellis Stevens, and William Rogers, gent. upon an indictment for the murther of Mrs. Sarah Stout, a Quaker before Mr. Baron Hatsell, at Hertford assizes, July 18, 1699 : of which they were acquitted : with the opinions of the eminent physicians and chyrurgeons on both sides, concerning drowned bodies, delivered in the tryal and the several letters produced in court. Cowper, Spencer, 1669-1728, defendant. Marson, John, defendant. Stevens, Ellis, defendant. Rogers, William, Gent, defendant.
[2], 46 p.
Printed for Isaac Cleave ..., Matt. Wotton ..., and John Bullord ..., London : 1699.
Advertisement: p. 20. Reproduction of original in Huntington Library.
